---
name: js-stream-complete-stops
backends: [int, js]
---

# Stream.complete() stops emission on JS (js-algebraic-effects-residual)

`runStream`'s `Stream.emit` buffers directly into a side-channel that didn't observe
`Stream.complete()` (which set a separate local flag), so an `emit` after `complete()`
still landed in the collected source — `List(1, 2, 3)` instead of `List(1, 2)`. A
shared `_streamDone` flag now stops the side-channel too.

```scalascript
def readNumbers(shouldStop: Boolean): Int ! Stream[Int] =
  Stream.emit(1)
  Stream.emit(2)
  if shouldStop then Stream.complete()
  Stream.emit(3)
  3

val (full, c1) = runStream { readNumbers(false) }
println(full.runToList())

val (partial, c2) = runStream { readNumbers(true) }
println(partial.runToList())
```
